#Genus:

# Top N taxa
N <- 10
topg1 <- names(sort(taxa_sums(Kphyseq_norm_genus), decreasing = TRUE))[1:N]

N2 <- 20

N3 <- 30

# Calculate relative abundance
Kphyseq_norm_genus_prop <- transform_sample_counts(Kphyseq_norm_genus, function(x) x / sum(x) )

# Subset object to top N taxa
Kphyseq_norm_genus_prop_top <- prune_taxa(topg2, Kphyseq_norm_genus_prop)

Kphyseq_norm_genus_top <- prune_taxa(topg2, Kphyseq_norm_genus)

plot_abundance = function(Kphyseq_norm_genus_top, ylabn = "",
                          Facet = "Genus",
                          Color = "Genus"){
  mKphyseq = psmelt(Kphyseq_norm_genus_top)
  mKphyseq <- subset(mKphyseq, Abundance > 0)
  ggplot(data = mKphyseq,
         mapping = aes_string(x = "owner", y = "Abundance",
                              color = Color, fill = Color)) +
    geom_violin(fill = NA) +
    geom_point(size = 1, alpha = 0.3,
               position = position_jitter(width = 0.3)) +
    facet_wrap(facets = Facet) + ylab(ylabn) +
    scale_y_log10()
}

KphyseqRAg = transform_sample_counts(Kphyseq_norm_genus_top, function(x){x / sum(x)})
KphyseqRAg1 = transform_sample_counts(Kphyseq_norm_genus, function(x){x / sum(x)})

    scale_y_log10()
